    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-30T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">888.2553/7–3054: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 486<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom (<persName
                            corresp="#p_AWW1" type="from">Aldrich</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d486fn1">Repeated to Tehran.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-30T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 30, 1954—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>549. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 541, July 30.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d486fn2">In telegram 541 Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_AWW1"
                            >Aldrich</persName> informed the Department and Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_HLW1">Henderson</persName> that the <gloss target="#t_AIOC1"
                            >AIOC</gloss> directors the previous day had considered the Iranian
                        compensation offer; that he, <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">Aldrich</persName>,
                        believed the <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> had decided to accept the
                        present offer if necessary but hoped to raise the amount by five million
                        pounds and to shorten the payment period. If this effort failed, however, it
                        was <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">Aldrich</persName>’s view that the British
                        would not allow the compensation issue to drag beyond the negotiation of the
                        consortium agreement. (888.2553/7–3054)</note> Foreign Office confirms
                    information contained first paragraph reference telegram. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSRB1">Stevens</persName> will attempt persuade Iranians to (1)
                    increase compensation to pounds 30 million, and (2) reduce payment period to 12
                    years. First payment would be due 2 years after date of agreement, with annual
                    payments next 10 years thereafter. Foreign Office points out this time period
                    not in conformity with point (3) US–UK memo of understanding <pb facs="1069"
                        n="1043" xml:id="pg_1043"/> (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 4178,
                    March 26, 1954) but hopes UK will not object, in view of much smaller sum than
                    originally contemplated.</p>
                <p>. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aldrich</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
